article.headline: George Mason 92, Iona 83
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Senior guard Mark Davis equaled his career-high 26 points and George Mason never trailed in beating Iona 92-83 Saturday and giving coach Jim Larranaga his 300th victory. Lamar Butler added 15 points, Jai Lewis had 12 points and 10 rebounds, and Raoul Heinen 11 points for the visiting Patriots (2-1), who shot 51.4 percent. Steve Burtt had 19 points, Ricky Soliver 15 points, and Greg Jenkins 13 points and 16 rebounds for the Gaels (1-2). This is the seventh season (102-75) at George Mason for Larranaga, whose 20 years as a head coach include stints at American International and Bowling Green. His career record is 300-244. Butler had 10 points and Iona committed 16 turnovers as the Patriots led 43-33 at halftime. The Gaels staged a 10-2 scoring run, capped by Anthony Bruin's basket, to cut the margin to 53-49 with 15:18 left. Trent Wurtz, who had nine points, scored with 6:41 left to give George Mason a 72-58 lead. Burtt's basket with 1:02 to go cut the Iona deficit to 83-78, but the Patriots closed the game with a 9-5 scoring edge. Steve Smith added 10 points and Bruin 10 for the Gaels, who committed 24 turnovers overall. Davis scored 26 points twice before, against Drexel and Towson, both last season.
